{"input": [{"role":"user","content":"Hi, I need help planning a weekend trip to Rome on a tight budget."},
{"role":"assistant","content":"Sure! What dates are you considering, what’s your approximate budget, and what do you care about most: food, sightseeing, or nightlife?"},
{"role":"user","content":"Two nights in May, budget around 300 euros total, I care most about sightseeing and good, cheap food."},
{"role":"assistant","content":"Great. I recommend a budget hotel or hostel near Termini or Trastevere, walking-based sightseeing (Colosseum, Forum, Vatican exteriors if tickets too expensive), and eating in local trattorias away from main tourist streets. You can also buy a transport pass if your hotel isn’t central. Want me to propose a sample two-day itinerary?"},
{"role":"user","content":"Yes, plus a rough cost breakdown so I know if 300 euros is realistic."}
]}

{"input":[{"role":"user","content":"Our team retrospective keeps going off-topic. Can you help me structure it better?"},
{"role":"assistant","content":"Yes. How long is the meeting, how many people attend, and what’s your main goal: venting, learning, or deciding concrete improvements?"},
{"role":"user","content":"One hour, 8 people. Goal is to agree on 1–3 improvements for next sprint, not just vent."},
{"role":"assistant","content":"A simple structure is: 10 minutes for check-in, 15 for 'What went well', 15 for 'What didn’t', and 20 for picking 1–3 improvement experiments with owners. Use a timer and a facilitator who gently parks off-topic items. Would that fit your culture or feel too rigid?"},
{"role":"user","content":"I like it, but I’m worried people will feel rushed."}
]}

{"input":[{"role":"user","content":"Can you summarize this internal discussion about whether to move our backend from monolith to microservices?"},
{"role":"assistant","content":"Yes. What’s your current pain: performance, deployment risk, team scaling, or something else?"},
{"role":"user","content":"Mostly deployment risk and slow releases. The transcript is long; people argue both for gradual modularization and for a big rewrite."}]}

{"input":[{"role":"user","content":"Summarize this coaching conversation between me and my manager about my career development."},
{"role":"assistant","content":"Happy to. Do you want the summary to emphasize feedback, agreed goals, or action items?"},
{"role":"user","content":"Focus on goals and concrete next steps, but keep key feedback."}]}

{"input":[{"role":"user","content":"Here is a long customer-support chat about a billing dispute. I want a compact summary for our internal CRM notes."},
{"role":"assistant","content":"Okay. Should the summary emphasize root cause, customer sentiment, and resolution details?"},
{"role":"user","content":"Yes, especially what we promised and any follow-up tasks."}]}

{"input":[{"role":"user","content":"Can you summarize a 100-message mentorship chat into something I can review before my next 1:1?"},
{"role":"assistant","content":"Yes. I’ll identify who said what, main themes, key feedback, and any action items you agreed on. After you paste it, do you want the output more like bullet-point notes or a narrative summary?"},
{"role":"user","content":"Bullet-style notes, but please keep important context and decisions."}]}
